<TITLE> Dhaka seeks UN support for trying war crimes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 26 (bdnews24.com)Foreign minister Dipu Moni has sought UN support for the trial of war criminals, said a foreign ministry press statement on Monday. "We have  had talks on trial of war criminals," UN resident coordinator Renata Lok Dessallien told reporters after calling on the minister. Dessallien said the UN would examine how it could help in this regard if the government sought UN support. "The minister said the government was committed to bringing war criminals to justice," said the foreign ministry statement. The Awami League in its election manifesto pledged to bring war criminals to justice if voted to power. Foreign minister Dipu Moni also briefed the UNDP representative about the status of the ordinances issued by the caretaker government. "She hoped that the ordinance on establishment of the National Human Rights Commission would be adopted by Parliament," the statement said. The UN coordinator in Dhaka expressed concern about violations of human rights in Bangladesh, and said that she was happy to see return of democratic rule. bdn
